You know, spent the 48 hours and came up with a thing and then pitched it to Ubisoft and turned it into a game or something.

15
00:01:02,827 --> 00:01:09,733
Rather, what we were trying to do was take inspiration from Game Jam techniques and Game Jam culture

16
00:01:10,634 --> 00:01:17,859
and find a path to adapt that and scale that to AAA game development and the conception of a new AAA IP.

17
00:01:20,044 --> 00:01:24,728
And a few months ago, I had the honor and privilege of announcing this IP to the world

18
00:01:24,788 --> 00:01:30,012
at E3, where I got to go up and share the fruits of our labor with everyone.

19
00:01:30,592 --> 00:01:35,436
And I couldn't be more proud of the work that the team has done to create this.

20
00:01:35,476 --> 00:01:40,420
And I can't wait for, you know, we only gave a little snippet of what we're doing, and

21
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:41,621
I can't wait for everyone to see more.

22
00:01:43,566 --> 00:01:50,528
This is an IP that has a lot of innovation throughout, and at the core of that is this

23
00:01:50,968 --> 00:01:58,911
completely modular peripheral where you're able to add on wings and weapons and parts

24
00:01:59,011 --> 00:02:02,913
and everything, and everything you add on is instantly recreated in the game, and it

25
00:02:02,953 --> 00:02:04,393
totally changes the way that you play.

26
